&lt;pre class=&quot;code_block&quot; style=&quot;margin: -10px 0px -30px 0px; line-height: .9em&quot;&gt;include_once '&lt;span style=&quot;color: red;&quot;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;home/mediqxX/public_html/php/db_connect.php';&lt;/pre&gt;<br />
<br />
Otherwise without the &lt;span style=&quot;color: red;&quot;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; the server is going to be interpreting the home directory as a relative instead of a full path, and won't find the &lt;strong&gt;db_connect.php&lt;/strong&gt; script . However once you've included the correct file, more than likely you're going to get the generic 500 error again stating it can't find your custom 500.shtml error page.<br />
<br />
